The paper deals with the formal verification of security protocols, which is a topic that falls under the category of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR). The paper also introduces partial order reduction techniques, which are a well-known optimization technique in the field of model checking (cs.LO). The paper mentions the implementation of the reductions in a tool, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of "Programming Languages" (cs.PL) or "Software Engineering" (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the exploration of traces of concurrent processes, which is a topic that falls under the category of "Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing" (cs.DS).
